        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[The new pull-request challenge (club)]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[Recently I saw that the <a href="https://pullrequest.club/">PullRequest.Club</a> closed on January 1st. It's a pity as it was a good idea. But don't worry, the new PRC is here. Less organized but here. The challenge is to send a PR to <b>any</b> CPAN module once a week and share the link to it on <a href="https://github.com/szabgab/perlweekly/issues/633">this issue</a>. (see my first comments on that issue). If you have never contributed to an open source project or if you have never sent a PR, don't worry. I organize live online sessions where I demonstrate the whole process as I am working on a project. You can watch. You can ask question. You can learn. Then you can implement and send your own PRs. Check the events <a href="https://luma.com/perl-maven">here</a>!]]></description>
            <pubDate>2026.01.05</pubDate>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://osdc.code-maven.com/perl</guid>
            <link>https://osdc.code-maven.com/perl</link>
            
            
            
            <author><![CDATA[gabor_szabo]]></author>
            
                
            
            
        </item>
        
